@node "NList.mcc" "NList.mcc"

                                 @{b}NList.mcc@{ub}
                         ę 1996-1998 Gilles Masson


           That MCC public custom class is very similar to the
           MUI's list class.

           It handles directly most attributes which are handled
           by Listview in the original couple List/Listview.

           The NListview exist anyway to provide a complete
           object with scrollbars, so you should use it as child
           of NListview. Anyway, you can use NList without NListview
           if you don't want any builtin scrollbar.

                               Gilles Masson,
                          Les Balcons d'Antipolis
                                   Bloc C
                           15, Traverse du Barri
                               06560 VALBONNE
                                   FRANCE

                     e-mail:  masson@iutsoph.unice.fr
@endnode

@node "TextEditor.mcc" "TextEditor.mcc"

                              @{b}TextEditor.mcc@{ub}
                           ę 1997 Allan Odgaard


TextEditor.mcc is a fast multiline stringgadget. It can hold quite large texts
without noticeable slowdowns. It supports the clipboard, it can show text with
different styles, alignments and colors. It can hold separators, it has
multilevel undo/redo and it can easily be configured to use an external spell
checker for type'n'spell and word guessing.

The gadget is copyrighted 1997 by Allan Odgaard, but licenced by Finale
Development Inc.

                                Allan Odgaard
                               Dagmarsgade 36
                             DK-2200 Copenhagen

                             email: Duff@DIKU.DK

                    url: http://www.DIKU.dk/students/duff/
@endnode

@node "TearOff.mcc" "TearOff.mcc"

                              @{b}TearOff libraries@{ub}
                           ę 1999 Szymon Ulatowski

    This class allows the MUI applications to create special groups called 
  TearOffPanels. They can be freely arranged by the user, dragged outside the
  window or hidden. Panel layout is automaticaly stored and reused next time.
   If you don't like standard TearOff frames and images, you can reconfigure
                  the appearance with MUI Preferences program. 

                          email: szulat@amiga.org.pl

              support site: http://amiga.org.pl/~szulat/tearoff/
@endnode

