@node "History" "History"

    @{b}Version 1.0 (8.6.1998)@{ub}

       - First public release

    @{b}Version 1.1 (17.6.1998)@{ub}

       - Fixed: The bug in the list sorting, when the list was empty.
       - Fixed: Now the songplayer export works. Songplayer's playlist
                and audio database have different formats.
       - User can choose, what he/she wants to the MPEG audio list.
       - Some assembler optimizations
       - New button graphics. Thanks to Jukka Heikkilń

    @{b}Version 1.5 (17.7.1998)@{ub}

       - HTML export.
       - Now user can save HTML and custom export settings.
       - Configurable TAG to filename conversion.
       - Now the directory reading don't add the whole path to the filenames.
       - The genre label is not ghosted any more.
       - Fixed the bug in the short help.

    @{b}Version 1.51 (2.9.1998)@{ub}

       - Fixed the bug in the genre list.

    @{b}Version 1.7 (23.10.1998)@{ub}

       - Now the genre list is sorted.
       - Multiselect:
           o writing, reading and removing the Tag
           o Tag -> Comment conversion
           o Tag -> File name conversion
           o File name -> Tag conversion
       - Configurable TAG to comment conversion

    @{b}Version 1.71 (2.11.1998)@{ub}

       - Fixed some translation bugs.
       - In the HTML table export there is defaults for the header and the
         footer.

    @{b}Version 1.72 (3.11.1998)@{ub}

       - German catalog. Thanks to Georg Rottlaender.
       - Fixed: There was some problems with keyboard shortcuts in the HTML
                export table settings.

    @{b}Version 1.73 (21.1.1999)@{ub}

       - French catalog. Thanks to Pascal Chiozzi.
       - Czech catalog. Thanks to Boleslav Kristen.
       - Better environment saving. (now uses MUI's Export and Import methods)
       - Now user can choose which fields of the tag will be copied in
         the multiselect tag writing.

    @{b}Version 1.75 (11.6.1999)@{ub}

       - GUI uses TearOff.mcc. Thanks to Szymon Ulatowski.
       - Added new genres
       - When user has multiselected files and wants to write the tag,
         a window appears and asks which tags will be writed and which will
         stay unchanged.
       - Different preferences saving system (not anymore own drawer in ENV: )

@endnode

